title: Proper vs. Improper Plant Growth
description: The image illustrates two scenarios for plant growth. On the left, a plant with a capped top is shown with a red 'X', indicating improper growth. On the right, a plant with a curved top and a protective sleeve is shown with a green check mark, indicating proper growth. Both scenarios are depicted under sunlight.

title: Open Book with Illustrations
description: An open book displaying pages filled with text in an unknown script, accompanied by illustrations of three objects that resemble candles or lamps. The pages have a yellowed appearance, suggesting age.

title: Plant Growth Stages
description: An illustration showing the stages of plant growth. The image depicts several green shoots emerging from the soil, each at different angles and heights, with roots visible below the surface. A sun is shining in the background, indicating a light source.

title: Root Growth Stages
description: An illustration showing the stages of root growth in plants. The image depicts several green shoots emerging from the soil, each with a different root structure. The roots are shown branching out, and the shoots have varying shapes at their tips, indicating different stages of development.

title: Plant Growth and Cell Expansion
description: The image illustrates a seedling emerging from the soil, with a focus on the root and shoot. An inset shows a close-up of plant cells, highlighting their structure and the process of cell expansion, which is crucial for plant growth.
